Sleep, Sisters and Sara's<br/><br/>RIIINNNGG RRRRIIIIIINNNNGGGG!!!
<br /><br />Nate is woken up with a start as his bedside phone starts ringing right beside his ear. With a groan he reaches over and picks it up, almost dropping it as he brings it to his ear.
<br /><br />&quot;Uuugggh, thanks for waking me up.&quot; He was a little too tired for the formality of a proper greeting.
<br /><br />&quot;WAKING YOU UP?!?&quot; He recognized that voice, as high pitched and squealy as it was. It was Nicole, his sister. &quot;You were supposed to pick me up 15 minutes ago, remember?&quot; Nicole was 18 and living on her own, 
<br />but she still didn't have a car, so Nate had to drive her wherever she needed to go, in this case, shopping.
<br /><br />&quot;Aw damnnit...look give me 15 minutes OK? I'll give you an extra half hour shopping, deal?&quot; There was a silence on the other end until...
<br /><br />&quot;Fine, but only 15 minutes OK?&quot; Although he knew that if he showed up in another 30 minutes she would be mad sure, but she'd get over it, after all, she knows he's her only ride.
<br /><br />&quot;15 minutes, count on it.&quot;
<br /><br /><span class="textAlign textAlignCenter">--------------------------------------------------------------25 minutes later-----------------------------------------------------------------------</span>
<br /><br />Nate pulled up into Nicole's apartment building at 20 miles over the speed limit, he was already 10 minutes late and didn't want to waste any more time. He had heard that old saying far too many times:
<br /><br />Hell hath no wrath like a woman scorned
<br /><br />Running up to the intercom and pressing &quot;Rider&quot; he waited for her to answer. Unsurprisingly, she answered right away, she must have been waiting by the door.
<br /><br />&quot;You do realize I get an extra hour now right?&quot;
<br />With a sigh, he pushed the intercom
<br />     &quot;Fine, just get down here.&quot; he went back to the car and started it up, he wanted to get this done as soon as possible. He loved his sis of course, but being her chauffeur wasn't exactly his dream job. He turned his rear-view mirror so he could see just how bad he looked, and surprisingly it wasn't that bad. The bags under his blue eye's weren't as bad as he thought they were, his blond hair was still wet from the shower, but he just put a hat over it and no one will know the difference.
<br /><br />Nicole walked out looking great, as usual. She always fussed about her looks, spending hours getting ready to go out, when she didn't really need to. Her dark hair was naturally straight, but she would curl it, her chestnut brown eyes were gorgeous on their own, but she would put on liner, eye shadow, mascara, the works. The list goes on and on, and she came off looking just as beautiful as she started out in Nate's opinion.
<br /><br /><span class="textAlign textAlignCenter">----------------------------------------------------------------5 minutes later----------------------------------------------------------------------</span>
<br /><br />They parked in the middle of downtown and began their sweep, they hit almost every clothing store they saw. Now that she knew she had an extra hour nothing was going to slow her down.
<br /><br />They came to this one store and she ran inside, when he walked in he realized why. This was the megamart of fashion stores, bigger than any he's seen before. By the time he walked in she was already making her way through the racks, picking out more and more clothes. With a sigh, he went and sat down on the couch, obviously put there for boyfriends while their girlfriends spent their many hours in here.
<br /><br />He looked at the coffee table in front of him and saw a bunch of sports magazines, a couple Penthouses...definitely made for boyfriends. He reached out and picked up one of the football magazines and started reading. Before he could flip to an article, a voice came from behind him.
<br /><br />&quot;Wow, you actually didn't pick the Penthouse, now that's a surprise.&quot; He turned around to see one of the employees standing behind him, and quite frankly, she was gorgeous. &quot;I guess you don't want your girlfriend seeing you huh?&quot;
<br /><br />He looked at her in awe, she really was beautiful, her red hair flowed onto her white dress shirt uniform, which was quite flattering on her. She smiled at him and his heart skipped a beat. 
<br /><br />&quot;Actually I don't have a girlfriend, I drove my sister here.&quot; and then when the thought struck him, he added &quot;I have to say, I didn't know that they had models working here, otherwise I would come here a lot more often.&quot;
<br /><br />She laughed, a cute laugh, but not too pixie-ish. &quot;Well I didn't know that.......sorry I got nothing.&quot; Then they both laughed, and she came and sat down beside him. 
<br /><br />&quot;So,&quot; he said &quot;Are you really allowed to come and talk to customers? Or brother's of customers for that matter.&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Well buy something, then I'll have an excuse to talk to you.&quot; she let out a giggle &quot;Actually I'm on my break, so I'm free to talk to whoever I want thank you very much.&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;So you came and chose me? I feel honored&quot; he said, giving her a small little bow
<br /><br />&quot;Very funny smarty pants. Actually my break is for about another 20 minutes, do you want to go grab a coffee?&quot; Then she gave him that smile, and he knew he couldn't say no. He got up and started to walk out the door, when she said &quot;By the way, what's your name?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Nate, yours?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;I'm Sara, nice to meet you Nate.&quot; and she kissed him on the cheek...he felt himself blush.
<br /><br /><span class="textAlign textAlignCenter">-------------------------------------------------------30 minutes later--------------------------------------------------------------------------</span>
<br /><br />Nate looked at his watch, and saw that Sara's break was over 10 minutes ago. &quot;Oh wow, you really have to get back...but hey, are you free for dinner tonight?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Wow you don't waste any time do you? Yeah I'm free, what do you say 6:00 at the Copper Ladel?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;You realize it's usually the guy who makes that decision right?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Well have you been there before?&quot;
<br /><br />Nate thought for a second, he hadn't actually been there, all his years of living in Newensville and he had never been there. &quot;Uhh, no I haven't.&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Well then you don't know how good it is, so that's why I'm making the arrangements&quot; She smiled that 'I-know-you-have-nothing-to-say-to-that' smile and leaned in and kissed him on the cheek. Their heads refused to part from each other, so he went and kissed her other cheek. Still, their heads didn't part, he sat there staring into her eyes, not knowing what to do. With nowhere else to go, he leaned in and pecked her on the lips, and as he parted, she moved closer in, and connected with him open mouth on open mouth. Before he could even realize what had happened, it was over, and she put a finger to his mouth and said 
<br /><br />&quot;See you later lover boy&quot;

Restless Passions: Chapter Two<br/><br/>&quot;Wait..what...what did you say?&quot;
<br /><br />Ben stared into his brother's eyes, once so full of hopes and dreams, now faded by the years and years of rejection. But he noticed that there was a new spark, a faint glimmer in the storm clouds. It had been years since Ryan had a steady job, Ben could only hope that spark meant that had changed.
<br /><br />&quot;I need a place to stay,&quot; said Ryan timidly, &quot;I just got a job at this new firm in town, and I'm going to need a place to stay so I can save up some money...&quot;
<br /><br />Ryan had passed the bar exam about 2 years ago, but he had still not been able to find a steady job. It wasn't because he was a bad lawyer, but he had very strong morals. If he found out that the firm he was working at represented some unsavory types, he sent in his two weeks notice. Which basically ruled out...well every law firm.
<br /><br />Ben looked into his brother's eyes again, he knew that he probably should say no because of Alyssa, she was stressed out enough recently and didn't need some stranger in the house (they hadn't been dating that long so her and Ryan had never met). But when he looks at that hope in his eyes...
<br /><br />&quot;Of course you can, how could I say no to you?&quot; Ben said, putting his arm around his little brother &quot;Besides, it's Older Brother Commandment #271: When thy brother needeth a roof over his head, thou must provide&quot;
<br /><br />Ryan laughed, he always laughed at Ben's 'Older Brother Commandments', they had been going on since they were both kids. Ben was only a year older than Ryan, and never held little baby Ryan in his arms, but he took care of him as if he had. 
<br /><br />&quot;You never told me any of the younger brother commandments, are there any?&quot; asked Ryan, and then it was Ben's turn to have a laugh. 
<br /><br />&quot;Well let's see, there's Commandment #33: Thou shalt not stealeth thy brother's wench. These commandments are politically incorrect if you didn't notice, they were written a long, long time ago. Commandment #17: Thou shalt not covet thy brother's Ox, cart, or Plasma TV&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;So much for being written a long time ago, did they have Plasma TV's back in the day of the Commandments?&quot; asked Ryan, trying to go along with the joke.
<br /><br />&quot;Well not as we know them today of course, back then they were jesters that performed for the rich folk&quot; replied Ben, as he led Ryan up the stairs and towards the guest room. &quot;So tell me, where's this new job? Have you made sure they haven't represented any evil men who steal little old ladies groceries?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;First off,&quot; began Ryan, &quot;the man was evil, I've looked into his eyes and wanted to run for my life. Secondly, he stole her entire cart of groceries! Would you work for a company that helped that guy get off the hook?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Ryan, Ryan, Ryan, Ryan. When will you ever learn that being a lawyer is not a pretty thing? You are going to have to defend some people who aren't crucifix-carrying priests.&quot; 
<br /><br />&quot;No it's not that...I just want to know I'm doing good work you know? Not getting criminals out from behind bars.&quot; 
<br /><br />Ben sighed as he stepped through the door of the guest bedroom, he led Ryan inside and gave him a quick tour.
<br /><br />&quot;Well here you are, all the comforts of home. You have a bed...a table BESIDE the bed....and a closet...enjoy!&quot;
<br /><br />The room that Alyssa is staying in now used to be the guest bedroom, and since she moved in it dropped the word 'guest' from it's title. Ben wanted to have a guest bedroom around somewhere, so he took an empty room and threw a bed in it, turns out it was a good idea.
<br /><br />&quot;I'll take you thrift store shopping once you get your first paycheck, we'll get you some furniture in here. So back to my question, is this a good job you have?&quot;
<br /><br />Ryan flopped down on the bed, and as he sat up, Ben saw that the spark was leaving his eyes, and before he opened his mouth, Ben knew the answer.
<br /><br />&quot;Well yeah...kinda....the lady who interviewed me is nice, and she said that most of their clients are good people.&quot;
<br /><br />To save the trouble of actually continuing the conversation, Ben played it out in his head:
<br /><br /><em>And what about the rest of their clients? Did you ask about them?
<br /><br />No...
<br /><br />So they're probably all liars, killers and grocery vigilantes?
<br /><br />Yeah...
<br /><br />You're not going to last more than a month are you?
<br /><br />No...</em>
<br /><br />Ben looked at his watch, he had 20 minutes to get to work.
<br /><br />&quot;Look Ryan, I have to head out, but make yourself at home and I'll lend you one of my suits for your first day OK?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;OK, listen Ben I just wanted to say...well you know you didn't have to let me...&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;You're welcome&quot; said Ben, simply smiling at his younger brother.
<br /><br />&quot;Thanks&quot; Ryan replied, returning the smile from his older brother.
<br /><br />As Ben grabbed his toast, he realized that he never told Ben about Alyssa living here as well. Stepping out the front door he thought:
<br /><br /><em>Well this is going to make for an interesting introduction</em>

Restless Passions: Chapter Three<br/><br/>Sandy pulled her car into the parking lot and slammed her head against the steering wheel. It had been a long day, a day of fake smiles, lying and overdone make up. 
<br /><br />In other words, a job interview.
<br /><br />Her roommate had told her about it, the law firm where she works at had just fired a secretary, and the position was now open. Sandy knew nothing about the law, but Odette replied with something like this:
<br /><br />&quot;Law? You don't need to know anything about law! All you have to be able to do is remember what kind of coffee your boss likes and know how to suck up.&quot;
<br /><br />So she went into the interview thinking they were just going to ask a few simple questions, look over her resume and send her back out the door...
<br /><br />Yeah right.
<br /><br />They asked her a bunch of questions like:
<br /><br />'If two people get divorced, who has the automatic right to the children? Mother or Father?'
<br /><br />'What states still allow the death penalty?'
<br /><br />And so many more. Sandy knew none of them, she guessed on the divorce one, and said Texas and Alabama for the death penalty. She had no clue but figured that those two states out of any would still allow it.
<br /><br />She unlocked the door to her apartment and, with a sigh, pushed it open. Kicking off her shoes she grudgingly walked into the living room and dropped down onto the couch. 
<br /><br /><em>How could I be so stupid? I could never work at a firm, I don't know anything about...well anything. 
<br />Well isn't this a lovely sight? Here I am sitting at a crappy apartment, without a job, without money, and without a boyfriend. Don't I just have the greatest life ever?</em>
<br /><br />She turned on the TV and laid her head down on the couch, maybe she could just sleep and dream of a life where everything was going right................
<br /><br /><span class="textAlign textAlignCenter">___________________________________________</span>
<br /><br />&quot;Honey I'm home!&quot; said her husband, stepping through the door in his sharp black suit and leather briefcase. The twins ran up to him first and hugged him around his legs. They couldn't be more than 6 years old, and they screamed &quot;Daddy daddy daddy!!!&quot;
<br /><br />She walked up to meet him and gave him a quick kiss on the cheek. 
<br /><br />&quot;How was work baby?&quot; 
<br /><br />&quot;You'll never guess what happened. I made partner!&quot; he said, as he took off his jacket and showed off his muscular frame confined in a tight dress shirt.
<br /><br />&quot;Oh my god! Honey that's fantastic!&quot; she screamed as she jumped into his arms &quot;Now we'll finally be able to buy that house that we've been dreaming of getting!&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;I know, and I couldn't have done it without you hun, you carried me through all those hard years of being a starting lawyer. I love you baby.&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;I love you too my prince&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;I love you more&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;No I love YOU more&quot;
<br /><br />And so the argument ensued, as they playfully jabbed each other back and forth. Never had two people been more in love than this, you could just feel the warmth radiating off of them. After the argument ended, they agreed that they both loved each other an equal, unmeasurable amount. 
<br /><br />&quot;Supper's almost ready, I'll just go wash up&quot; she said, giving him another peck on the cheek, this time however he pulled her in for a long, amazing kiss. After 8 years of marriage, he could still send electricity all the way down to her toes.
<br /><br />Blushing, she made her way into the bathroom, which was furnished with gold-plated faucets, an ivory toilet and bathtub, and on the walls were various sketches that the kids made, all done with crayon of course. 
<br /><br />Placing her hands in the sink, she soaped up, scrubbed and rinsed. The wedding ring on her finger glimmered with perfection, as a large diamond sat in the center of a 24 karat gold ring. 
<br /><br />She looked up into the mirror and fixed her hair, which she noticed wasn't blond, like it is supposed to be...and the face wasn't hers either.
<br /><br />She realized with horror, that it was Odette she was looking at in the mirror.
<br /><br />&quot;Sweetie?&quot; came the call from the kitchen, and again &quot;Sweetie? You there? Wake up, WAKE UP!&quot;
<br /><br /><span class="textAlign textAlignCenter">_______________________________________</span> 
<br /><br />&quot;WAKE UP!!&quot;
<br /><br />Sandy was back lying on her couch, remote still in her hand, and Odette standing over her. So much for dreaming of a perfect life.
<br /><br />&quot;Well hun?&quot; asked the bright eyed Odette &quot;How did the interview go? Do you think you got the job?&quot;
<br /><br />Sandy sat up on the couch and ran her fingers through her hair, which was once again blond, and messed up from lying on the couch for what she figured was about 5 or 6 hours.
<br /><br />&quot;If I got it then your firm is a joke, the interview was horrible, she asked me a bunch of questions I didn't know the answer to, I sounded like an idiot, and to top it all off, I'm pretty sure she didn't like me.&quot; Sandy began to stand up, &quot;I need a drink&quot;
<br /><br />Odette pushed her back down onto the couch, &quot;No no no, I can't have you drunk sweetie, what if they call and ask you to come back?&quot;
<br /><br />Sandy couldn't help but laugh at that, after that horrendous interview, Odette still thinks she has a shot. Forever the optimist is what she is. &quot;Listen, I have no job, no money, you've been paying my half of the rent for a good 3 months now, I haven't had a date in months, I don't even know if I'm capable of flirting anymore, just let me have a...&quot;
<br /><br />The phone rang.
<br /><br />They both went silent and stared at the ringing contraption sitting 2 feet in front of them. 
<br /><br />It rang again.
<br /><br />Sandy saw her dream coming back to life, the husband, the kids, the house, the money!
<br /><br />It rang a third time.
<br /><br />&quot;ANSWER IT!&quot; screamed Odette
<br /><br />Sandy attacked the phone and pulled it to her ear
<br /><br />&quot;Hello?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Yes...&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;No I understand...&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;No no it's perfectly fine...&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Thank you very much, good bye.&quot;
<br /><br />She put the phone down and sat back on the couch, picked up the remote and started watching TV. As she flipped through channels, Odette was standing just to the side with her face frozen in the screamer position.
<br /><br />&quot;Well?&quot; she finally asked &quot;What did they say?&quot;
<br /><br />&quot;Oh right, they told me that they had about 30 applicants, it would not have been very easy to get the job anyways. They said that they think I got the hardest interviewer, she asked questions that no one else asked...oh yeah, and they told me I start tomorrow!&quot;
<br /><br />They both screamed.
